## About
This repository contains a Task Management application designed for learning and rapid prototypes. It separates concerns with a Laravel API (backend) and a React + TypeScript SPA (frontend). The API exposes endpoints for authentication and task management; the frontend is a Vite app that consumes the API.

## âœ¨ Features
- User registration & login (token-based authentication)
- Protected API endpoints (Laravel Sanctum / token-based)
- Task CRUD: create, read, update, delete
- Task statuses: `pending`, `in_progress`, `done`
- Each user manages their own tasks
- Paginated task listing with search & filter
- Responsive UI built with Tailwind CSS
- Docker Compose for local development
- Environment-aware configuration (SQLite for dev, MySQL for prod)
- Basic API documentation and examples

## ðŸ›  Tech Stack
### Backend
- Laravel 10.x
- Laravel Sanctum (API authentication)
- PHP 8.1+
- SQLite (development) / MySQL (production)
- Composer

### Frontend
- React 18
- TypeScript 5.x
- Vite
- Tailwind CSS
- Axios
- React Router
- React Hot Toast (notifications)

### DevOps & Tools
- Docker & Docker Compose
- Git
- Postman / Insomnia (suggested for API testing)

## Architecture
- Backend: RESTful API serving JSON, authenticates requests and scopes tasks to users.
- Frontend: Single Page App (Vite) that talks to the API using Axios, stores tokens (cookies or localStorage depending on setup), and provides UI for task management.

---

## ðŸš€ Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Docker & Docker Compose (recommended)
- OR:
  - PHP 8.1+
  - Composer
  - Node.js 18+
  - npm / pnpm / yarn
  - A database (SQLite/MySQL)

Clone the repo:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/ayaos123/task-management-app.git
cd task-management-app
```

### Using Docker (Recommended)
A Docker Compose setup is provided for easy local development.

1. Copy example env files (if included) or create minimal .env files for both backend and frontend:
   - backend: `./backend/.env` (or root .env if monorepo)
   - frontend: `./frontend/.env`

2. Start services:
```bash
# Use docker compose v2 syntax
docker compose up -d --build
```

3. Run migrations & seeders (run artisan inside the app container):
```bash
# If the service in docker-compose is named `app` or `backend`:
docker compose exec app php artisan migrate --seed --force
# or
docker compose exec backend php artisan migrate --seed --force
```

4. (Optional) Create a default user via seeder or tinker:
```bash
docker compose exec app php artisan db:seed --class=UserSeeder
```

5. Open the frontend (if served by Vite in container) â€” typical URL:
http://localhost:5173
Or use the host/ports configured in docker-compose.

Notes:
- Service names depend on the included docker-compose file. Replace `app`/`backend` with the correct service name in your compose file.

### Manual / Local Setup (no Docker)

Backend:
```bash
# in backend folder
cp .env.example .env
composer install
php artisan key:generate
# Configure DB in .env (use sqlite for quick start)
touch database/database.sqlite
# .env
# DB_CONNECTION=sqlite
# DB_DATABASE=/absolute/path/to/database/database.sqlite

php artisan migrate --seed
php artisan serve --host=0.0.0.0 --port=8000
```

Frontend:
```bash
# in frontend folder
cp .env.example .env
npm install
# set VITE_API_URL in .env to http://localhost:8000 (or your API URL)
npm run dev
# build for production
npm run build
```

---

## Environment

### Backend (.env) example
Below are the common vars you should configure in the backend `.env`:

```
APP_NAME="Task Management"
APP_ENV=local
APP_KEY=base64:GENERATED_BY_ARTISAN
APP_URL=http://localhost:8000

DB_CONNECTION=sqlite
DB_DATABASE=/absolute/path/to/database/database.sqlite
# or for mysql:
# DB_CONNECTION=mysql
# DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
# DB_PORT=3306
# DB_DATABASE=task_app
# DB_USERNAME=root
# DB_PASSWORD=secret

SANCTUM_STATEFUL_DOMAINS=localhost:5173
SESSION_DOMAIN=localhost
API_RATE_LIMIT=60

# If using JWT (optional)
# JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret_here
```

Remember to run:
```bash
php artisan key:generate
```

### Frontend (.env) example
For Vite, create `frontend/.env` or `.env.local`:

```
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
VITE_APP_NAME="Task Management"
```

The frontend uses VITE_API_URL to call the backend.

---

## Database & Seeding
- Migrations define `users` and `tasks` tables.
- Seeder(s) create demo users and sample tasks for development.

Commands:
```bash
# run migrations
php artisan migrate

# seed the database
php artisan db:seed

# rollback & migrate fresh
php artisan migrate:fresh --seed
```

If using Docker, run these commands inside the PHP/Laravel container (see Docker section).

---

## API Reference (common endpoints)
Base URL: /api

Authentication:
- POST /api/register
  - body: { name, email, password, password_confirmation }
  - response: user + token
- POST /api/login
  - body: { email, password }
  - response: user + token
- POST /api/logout
  - header: Authorization: Bearer <token>

Tasks (all routes require authentication):
- GET /api/tasks
  - params: page, per_page, status (pending|in_progress|done), q (search)
  - returns: paginated tasks for authenticated user
- POST /api/tasks
  - body: { title, description, status }
- GET /api/tasks/{id}
- PUT /api/tasks/{id}
  - body: { title?, description?, status? }
- DELETE /api/tasks/{id}

Example: create a task (curl)
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/tasks \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <your_token>" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"title":"New Task","description":"Details","status":"pending"}'
```

Pagination example:
- GET /api/tasks?page=1&per_page=10

Search & filter:
- GET /api/tasks?q=meeting&status=in_progress

Notes:
- The API returns standard HTTP status codes and JSON payloads.
- Ensure CORS & Sanctum settings allow your frontend domain.

---

## Frontend routes & behavior
Typical routes (subject to implementation):
- / â€” Dashboard / Task list (paginated)
- /login â€” Login page
- /register â€” Registration page
- /tasks/new â€” Create task
- /tasks/:id â€” View / edit task

Authentication:
- On login, the frontend stores the token (either cookie or localStorage based on config) and attaches it to requests (Authorization header or withCredentials for cookies).
- Protected routes redirect to /login when unauthenticated.

